reviews.review_text: Grateful Gobblers ! From The Ear Of The Goddess, (Thank You Betty) A Thanksgiving Treat From Gobbler Land. This Ones Gotta Be My Favorite Black Peter Ever. Jerry Wailin' And Playin' Some Grate Guitar Too. Due To Being Pulled Over By The Virginia State Police Found It Necessary To Ingest The Most Acid I Ever Et. (And That's A Sayin' Sumpthin'. Held Us Outside The Van For Over An Hour While I Watched Them Literally Turn Into Some Kinda Pork Monsters With Little Police Hats. Then They Followed Us All The Way To The Turn Into The Coliseum. Glad I Wasn't Driving'. Hippy Thanksgiving' Everybody !

Great Ship of Fools Great Ship of Fools! That's not a sentence that I write very often, but this one sparkles.

Rest of the show is great too, check out Dire Wolf in the first set. A lot of people still find it cool to dismiss '78 even with all these great boards circulating these days. Still my favourite year along with '77, sometimes I even like '78 better than '77, more peaks and troughs but the peaks are higher!

Sangria. WOW... This show is absolutely spectacular. I'm working my way through the April tour, and I just can't get enough of this sound. It's chunky, bitter, but so sweet. Like you're drinking a beautiful Sangria. Tropical.... 

Peace ~ Nick.
